## Prioritized Remediation

| Priority | Fix | Effort | Why |
|----------|-----|--------|-----|
| 1 | Remove `if/else` — split into two tests | Low | Hidden untested branch |
| 2 | Add assertions to `CompletesWithoutError` | Low | False pass risk |
| 3 | Replace `Thread.Sleep` with sync wait | Medium | Flaky + slow |
| 4 | Inline CSV data, remove file dependency | Low | Fails on every other machine |
| 5 | Replace try/catch with `Assert.ThrowsException` | Low | Cleaner, better failure messages |
| 6 | Name the magic numbers | Low | Unverifiable expectations |
| 7 | Assert on properties, not `ToString()` | Low | Brittle to format changes |
| 8 | Tag or split the 7-method workflow test | Medium | Hard-to-diagnose failures |
| 9 | Add assertion messages | Low | Unclear which assertion failed |
| 10 | Remove unused `_logger` | Trivial | Dead setup code |

8 of 9 test methods have at least one smell. The good news: most fixes are quick (swap a pattern, add a message, inline data). Tackling items 1–5 first will eliminate all the high-severity risks.
